        <name>8.3.1.2 Exercise linear system diagonal matrix</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solve the following system of equations:&lt;/p&gt;
\[ {@matA@} {@vecX@} = {@vecB@}.\] 

&lt;div&gt;\(X=\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&amp;nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We are given the system of equations:&lt;/p&gt;\[ {@matA@} {@vecX@} = {@vecB@}.\]&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt; The sytem reads

&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[\begin{matrix}
    {@a11@}x &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; {@vecB[1][1]@}  \\
    {@a22@}y &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; {@vecB[2][1]@}  \\
    {@a33@}z &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; {@vecB[3][1]@}  \\
\end{matrix}\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From which we can directly obtain
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="math display"&gt;\[x = {@ta[1][1]@}, \qquad y = {@ta[2][1]@} , \qquad z = {@ta[3][1]@}. \]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
